snippet.textDisplay:
Come on, Rian Johnson barely subverted expectations.
Episode 7 showed the Jedi temple destroyed and Luke on exile, Leia as having abandoned the New Republic, Han going back to his smuggler ways, and the empire fully rebuilt.

The only thing he did that I didn't expect on some level, was the pointless journey to the gambling planet, which was at least visually interesting, unlike 90% of episode 7.
Sure, ep7 had better story and execution, but it visually didn't feel like StarWars.
